FLAG CATALOG!

-h      Self explanatory, outputs the help message.

-f      Sets the fractal for the program, mandelbrot is always the default.
        Type it exactly as the name appears. This can be combined with
        -c (color) flag to get the output you actually want
        $ fracterm -f burning_ship

-c      Sets the coloring algorithm for the fractal you chose. DEM is almost
        always the one you want to choose, I added other options literally
        because I wanted variety. Therefore, default is DEM. You use it
        similarly to -f, type exactly as the name appears
        $ fracterm -c dwell

-i      Sets iterations, basically how long do we iterate a point for.
        Default is 5000, which I find to be a good value between performance
        for shallow zooms and details. If you choose zoom mode, or plan to
        go deep, set this up well above 10000. Obviously, the higher the
        iterations, the worse the performance
        $ fracterm -i 10000

-b      Sets bailout. With ascii graphics, you can't really tell the
        difference. But someone might want to play with it, so why not?
        I won't explain what a bailout is, go to dovskyi/docs to read
        about how fractal calculation works.
        $ fracterm -b 4

-m      This is important. -m sets the mode. For the most part, you just
        want to explore the fractal, pan the space, zoom in/out here and
        there. For this, choose "explore". You don't even need to choose 
        it, as it is the default.
        "zoom" is a mode if you want to continuously zoom into a single
        reference point. In the future it will lock you in place with 
        automatical zoom in/out. Obviously, you need to provide the
        reference point first.
        I'll work on it more later, no time right now 3:
        $ fracterm -m zoom 1.534 -0.0023



Full initialization examples:

$ fracterm 
Creates: Mandelbrot, DEM, explore mode, default variables

$ fracterm -f burning_ship -c dwell -i 8500
Creates: Burning ship, dwell, iterations set to 8500

$ fracterm -m zoom -1.789169018604823106674468341188838763817361836815 -0.000000339368515767182566028230266146812728348218894593 -i 15000
Creates: Mandelbrot, DEM, zoom mode with reference point at provided coordinates, 15000 iterations


